The original plan was just to use ultrasonic sensors so you could select a floor by waving your hand,
perfect for hospitals where you want to avoid contact.
But I figured it’d be cool to add voice control for people standing further back in the elevator.

I initially tried training a custom audio model to run directly on the ESP32,
but it just couldn't handle it. I really didn't want to take the easy route and just connect it to a phone's Bluetooth,
because I wanted the system to be completely independent.
My workaround was to run the Whisper ML model locally on my PC.
Now, the ESP32 just picks up the audio and shoots it over WiFi to my local server,
which does all the heavy lifting and translates the speech to text.
